  "text": "Finally, P (s i+1 |X, t i , s 1:i ) is defined using an LSTM-based acoustic encoder with input X, an LSTM-based label encoder with non-blank inputs s, and a feed-forward joint network combining outputs from the two encoders to produce predictions for all symbols s, including the blank symbol. The Forward-Backward algorithm can be used to calculate Eq. (7) efficiently during training, and Viterbi-based beam search (based on the argmax over possible alignments) can be used for decoding when W is unknown [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
